he\nstellar polar rotational period, suggesting the presence of a magnetic\nconnection between the planet and the stellar pole. If these periodicities\nrepresent an SPI signal, it is likely driven by a quasi-continuous form of\nheating (e.g., magnetic field stretching) rather than sporadic, hot, impulsive\nflare-like reconnections.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Nov 2022 10:19:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Apr 2023 13:29:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-27"}
