ely\ninflated. With a radius of 1.21 $R_{J}$ and mass of 0.52 $M_{J}$, NGTS-24b has\na radius larger than expected from non-inflated models but its radius is\nsmaller than the predicted radius from current Bayesian inflationary models.\nFinally, NGTS-25b is intermediate between the inflated and non-inflated cases,\nhaving a mass of 0.64 $M_{J}$ and a radius of 1.02 $R_{J}$. The physical\nprocesses driving radius inflation remain poorly understood, and by building\nthe sample of hot Jupiters we can aim to identify the additional controlling\nparameters, such as metallicity and stellar age.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Nov 2022 11:21:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-16"}
